commit 69ddbd7267f12f48f8f42d35d6d9e4e34bb6eb3c
Author: Finlay Phillips <finlayp32@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 3 20:41:34 2026 +0100

    Enhance file ingestion and processing capabilities
    
    - Implemented a check for null bytes in the first 512 bytes of files to identify binary content in `ingest_file_if_text`.
    - Updated `read_text_with_short_retry` to handle `ErrorKind::InvalidData` gracefully.
    - Expanded the list of supported text file extensions in `is_supported_text_path` to include additional formats such as JSON, CSV, SQL, and more.
    - Added a new function `has_null_bytes` to detect binary files based on null byte presence.
    - Introduced `bootstrap` module and integrated ONNX artifact bootstrap functionality in the main application.
    - Enhanced command-line help to include new `embedding-bootstrap` command.
    - Improved text cleaning in the processing pipeline to normalize Unicode and strip control characters.
    - Updated documentation to reflect changes in the system map and added details about the new ONNX artifact bootstrap feature.
    - Added new test workspace files for capture token and vector store metadata.

